product_name: NYX Professional MakeupSoft Matte Lip Cream Lightweight Liquid Lipstick
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackNYX Professional Makeup Soft Matte Lip Cream is a unique matte liquid lipstick with a creamy mousse texture delivering comfortable, long lasting lip color.
details: DetailsBenefitsCreamy liquid lipstick with a smooth velvety matte finishDurable and lightweight with a mousse texture that applies like silkThis lip cream is light on the lips, but heavy on the pigmentation with a sweetly scented formulaThis is the best long-lasting matte lipstick that will stay on throughout the dayThis plush matte lip cream comes in colors inspired by cities of the world - enjoy matte lips that are always soft, never dry, in rosy hues of Copenhagen, go nude in Abu Dhabi & blush all over in StockholmIncludes a soft wand applicator for precise applicationCruelty freeKey IngredientsEnriched with skin-smoothing silicones to nourish your lipsItem 2268526How To UseApply directly to dry, clean lips with included applicator. You can build up your coverage or layer different shades to achieve your desired finish. Use alone or with any NYX Professional Makeup lip liner for a more precise application.Pro Tip: Double up on lip cream layers to build a longer lasting application.IngredientsRome: Isohexadecane, Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Dimethicone, Beeswax / Cera Alba / Cire d'Abeille, Glyceryl Behenate / Eicosadioate, Talc, Cyclopentasiloxane, Propylene Carbonate, Silica, Methyl Methacrylate Crosspolymer, Aluminum Starch Octenylsuccinate, Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Barium Sulfate (CI 77120), Alumina, Phenoxyethanol, Flavor/Aroma, Benzyl Alcohol, Benzyl Benzoate, Benzyl Salicylate, Hexyl Cinnamal, Hydroxycitronellal. May Contain: Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Blue 1 Lake (CI 19140), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 (CI 15850), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410).
how_to_use: Apply directly to dry, clean lips with included applicator. You can build up your coverage or layer different shades to achieve your desired finish. Use alone or with any NYX Professional Makeup lip liner for a more precise application.Pro Tip: Double up on lip cream layers to build a longer lasting application.

reviews.headline: I love this lipstick so much! It's such a beautiful shade.

reviews.headline: It's just okay
reviews.comments: The only thing I liked about this is the color. It has a weird odor that I don't like. It takes two or three layers to get the desired look because it's so thin. It doesn't last last long. I should've taken it back for a refund but I just threw it away.

reviews.headline: They changed the formula
reviews.comments: I have been using these since o discovered them a couple years ago. Couldnt beat the price for such a great lip product, but ive recently noticed that the formula is thicker and more drying. This makes me very sad. Amsterdam is more bright orange than red. Alot of the nude colors are not POC as they are lighter than advertised on the tube. My favorite is still madrid

reviews.headline: Shade doesn't match
reviews.comments: I have a older bottle & I recently purchased a new one and its not even close, its about two shades brighter pink. So dissapointing

reviews.headline: My go to for years

reviews.headline: Shade doesn't match
reviews.comments: Formula is good but shade match isn't even close to what is shown in the tube and model swatches. Bought shade Cannes expecting a pink mauve but got a heavily cool toned purple?

reviews.headline: Color Isn't The Same Anymore
reviews.comments: They don't make Copenhagen the same anymoreüò´ The color is so different than what it was years ago. The color used to be a dark plum color, which matched the description and color of it's packaging. Now, it's more of a red. The lip liner is closer to the original color.

reviews.headline: Does not match what was advertised
reviews.comments: Although there is a great consistency and feels good on the lips it sadly does not match what was advertise. I ordered the color Copenhagen which looks like it will e a deep purple on the advertised pictures and the bottle itself but that was not the color of lipstick at all. The color was more of a bright red/dark blush color. This was quite disappointing because I was looking for the color that was advertised.

reviews.headline: Color doesn't match description

faceoff_positive.comments: The first matte lip cream I bought was in the color Ibiza and I was HOOKED. It is a beautiful deep coral color. I was so surprised at how ling wearing this product was and how great it felt on my lips. I went ahead and bought Istanbul, Prague, Addis Ababa, Monte Carlo, Morocco, Zurich, and Transylvania and plan on buying the rest because of the high quality and low price! These matte creams are not drying at all and do not feather on the lips like ither matte products do. Plus, the pigmentation is amazing! I LOVE NYX ‚ù§
faceoff_positive.headline: Best lip product EVER ‚ù§

faceoff_negative.comments: This product is only good if you have NO ridges or cracks in your lips. If you do, stay away from it and if you don't, try it out! I love the colors and the idea of it but it dries into your lip creases and makes them look awful. Its okay over lipstick with the megashine gloss ontop but its best to just skip this product if your lips aren't perfect.
